-- Bruederle Rejects Financial Transaction Tax, Passauer Reports
-- B y   N i k l a s   M a g n u s s o n
-- 2012-06-05T03:00:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-05/bruederle-rejects-financial-transaction-tax-passauer-reports.html
Rainer Bruederle, the floor chief of
the German Free  Democratic Party , has dismissed proposals for a
financial transaction tax, saying it would burden all citizens
and not financial markets,  Passauer Neue Presse  reported today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Niklas Magnusson in Hamburg at 
 nmagnusson1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
